# .python-version — pins the Python interpreter for this repository.
#
# WHAT THIS FILE IS FOR
#   pyenv (and compatible tools such as uv/pdm) read this file and automatically
#   select the version named below whenever you run `python` / `python3` inside
#   this project. This keeps every contributor, the editor (VS Code/Pylance),
#   and the type checker (mypy) on one interpreter, so installed packages and
#   stubs — e.g. reportlab and types-reportlab — resolve consistently.
#
# WHEN TO CHANGE THE VERSION
#   - Only when the project intentionally adopts a new Python release (a
#     dependency requires it, or to pick up security/bug fixes).
#   - Install the new version with pyenv first, then update the line below:
#         pyenv install --list      # see available versions
#         pyenv install <version>   # install it
#         (edit the version line below to match)
#   - Keep it in sync with CI (e.g. actions/setup-python) and the interpreter
#     VS Code selects, so local, CI, and editor all agree.
#   - After changing it, reinstall the Python deps in the new interpreter:
#         pip install -r utils/requirements.txt
#
# NOTE: pyenv ignores these comment lines. The single non-comment line below is
# the active version — keep exactly one version line.
3.14.2
